 Shows strong engagement within the team and across departments. Actively participates in discussions, contributes ideas, and fosters a positive and collaborative work culture.



2️⃣ Consistently Engaged (Exceeds Expectations)

> Demonstrates good team involvement and contributes positively to team activities. Always approachable and maintains healthy communication with peers and stakeholders.



3️⃣ Moderately Engaged (Meets Expectations)

> Participates regularly in team meetings and discussions. Could increase involvement in organization-wide initiatives and knowledge-sharing sessions to further enhance engagement.



4️⃣ Limited Engagement (Needs Improvement)

> Performs well in assigned tasks but could improve participation in team interactions and collaborative discussions. Encouraged to engage more actively in team forums and events.



5️⃣ Balanced but Reserved (Neutral/Stable Performer)

> Maintains a calm and professional demeanor within the team. Participates when required but can take more initiative in collaborative activities or group problem-solving sessions.



6️⃣ Improvement Needed (Below Expectations)

> While technically sound, tends to stay focused on individual tasks with limited engagement in broader team communication. Encouraged to show more proactive involvement in group activities and cross-team collaboration.
